<item>
            <title>[LU-17534] lctl map that maps to the actual mount instance internally</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17534</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Andreas&apos;s comment during a review(&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/53796).&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/53796).&lt;/a&gt;&#160; Opening an improvement LU so the idea does not get lost.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;That makes me wonder if it would be useful for users/scripts to be able to somehow call &quot;lctl get_param llite.$MOUNT.param&quot; and have lctl map that to the actual mount instance internally? &#160;For example, something like:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;# lctl get_param llite./mnt/testfs.pcc&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;would be mapped internally to be the equivalent of:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;# lctl get_param llite.testfs-ffff9ec607c56678.pcc&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code could key on &quot;./&quot; in the parameter name to do the llapi_getname() call. &#160;That gets tricky if there is a &apos;.&apos; inside the mount path, so it might need to try a few combinations of pathnames.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
